PHASE 1 – SECURITY GOALS CHECKLIST:
1. Identity & Access

 All endpoints require authentication by default

 OAuth2 / OIDC used (no password handling in app)

 Short-lived tokens + revocation support

 RBAC enforced server-side

 Admin actions explicitly gated & logged

 Tenant context resolved server-side (never from client)

2. Multi-Tenancy & Authorization

 Every request is scoped to a tenant

 Every DB table includes tenant_id

 No cross-tenant access possible

 Authorization checked on every state-changing action

 IDOR protections enforced everywhere

3. Data Protection

 TLS for all external & internal traffic

 Encryption at rest for DB & object storage

 Secrets never stored in code or repos

 Sensitive data excluded from logs

 Data collection minimized to necessity

4. Input & Application Logic

 All external input validated

 Strong typing preferred over dynamic parsing

 Safe error handling (no internal leaks)

 Business logic abuse considered & tested

5. Supply Chain & Dependencies

 Dependencies monitored for vulnerabilities

 Vulnerable deps blocked from release

 SBOM generated for every build

 Third-party code tracked and auditable

6.  CI/CD & Build Integrity

 CI pipelines isolated and ephemeral

 Secrets protected from untrusted PRs

 Only trusted branches can release artifacts

 All build artifacts are signed

 Artifact provenance is traceable

7. Infrastructure & Runtime

 Infrastructure defined as code

 Environments isolated (dev / stage / prod)

 Runtime behavior observable

 Unexpected behavior detectable & alerting enabled

8. Logging & Audit

 Auth events logged

 Admin actions logged

 Security events logged

 Logs protected from tampering

 Logs retained for investigation

9. Incident Readiness

 Security incidents detectable

 Credentials/tokens revocable

 Backups exist & are tested

 Incident response steps documented

 Post-incident review planned

10. Governance

 Security rules applied consistently

 Exceptions documented explicitly

 Security controls testable in CI

 Security debt tracked and revisited
